messages.content:
Here's a simple web app that allows you to type into a box and then responds in 20 different ways to indicate that it has no idea what you're saying. The HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are all embedded in a single code block.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Confused App</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        #inputBox {
            width: 300px;
            height: 100px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        #response {
            width: 300px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #fff;
            min-height: 100px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: white;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Confused App</h1>
    <textarea id="inputBox" placeholder="Type something..."></textarea>
    <button onclick="generateResponse()">Submit</button>
    <div id="response"></div>

    <script>
        const responses = [
            "I'm not sure what you mean.",
            "Could you clarify that?",
            "That's beyond my understanding.",
            "I have no idea what you're talking about.",
            "I'm lost here.",
            "Can you rephrase that?",
            "I'm not following you.",
            "That doesn't compute.",
            "I'm a bit confused.",
            "What do you mean by that?",
            "I'm not equipped to handle that.",
            "That's a mystery to me.",
            "I can't make sense of that.",
            "I'm scratching my head over here.",
            "That's a head-scratcher.",
            "I'm in the dark about that.",
            "I can't wrap my head around it.",
            "That's a puzzle I can't solve.",
            "I'm drawing a blank.",
            "I don't have the foggiest idea.",
            "That's a riddle I can't answer."
        ];

        function generateResponse() {
            const input = document.getElementById('inputBox').value;
            if (input.trim() === "") {
                document.getElementById('response').innerText = "Please type something!";
                return;
            }
            const randomResponses = [];
            for (let i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
                const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * responses.length);
                randomResponses.push(responses[randomIndex]);
            }
            document.getElementById('response').innerText = randomResponses.join('\n');
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions to Use:
1. Copy the entire code block above.
2. Paste it into a new file and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `confused_app.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser to use the app. Type something into the box and click the "Submit" button to see the responses.
